    Class Description
    CalypsoPo
    The CalypsoPo handles the Calypso SE characteristics such as: revision serial number session buffer limit TODO Complete with other PO features from the FCI and/or ATR
    PoSelector
    Specialized selector to manage the specific characteristics of Calypso POs
    PoTransaction
    Portable Object Secure Session.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    PoSelector.RevisionTarget
    Selection targets definition
    PoTransaction.CommunicationMode
    Two communication modes are available for the PO.
    PoTransaction.ModificationMode
    The modification mode indicates whether the secure session can be closed and reopened to manage the limitation of the PO buffer memory.
    PoTransaction.SamSettings
    List of SAM settings keys that can be provided when the secure session is created.
    PoTransaction.SessionAccessLevel
    The PO Transaction Access Level: personalization, loading or debiting.
    PoTransaction.SessionState
    The PO Transaction State defined with the elements: ‘IOError’, ‘SEInserted’ and ‘SERemoval’.
